The paper proposes a toolkit for creating tangible experiences using physiological signals, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions potential applications in education (STEM), medical applications, and entertainment, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), robotics (cs.RO), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
